Question 1 — Java: Find Frequent Words 
Write a Java method: 
List<String> findStopWords(String text, int k) 

The method should return all words that appear at least k times in the input text. 

Requirements: 

Words should be returned in the order of their first appearance. Use appropriate Java collections to count word frequency. Preserve insertion order when returning results. 

Example 

Input: 

text = "a b a c b a" 

k = 2 

 Output: 

[a, b] 

